{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1769528404,"nonce":"XAHcX076Fawt/+Fm3DwXczUGpGY=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87mJQDz","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/60","origin":"github"},"title":"Optimization: Consolidate Workspace Status Check Workflow","message":"# Workflow Optimization: Status Check\n\n## goal\nReduce the number of manual approvals and agent turns required to perform a full workspace status check (local + remote).\n\n## current_inefficiency\nCurrently, the agent must execute 5 separate commands to gather all necessary data:\n1.  `./.agent/scripts/status_report.sh` (Local Git Status)\n2.  `python3 .agent/scripts/list_overlay_repos.py` (Get Repo List)\n3.  `gh auth status` (Verify Auth)\n4.  `gh search prs ...` (Fetch PRs)\n5.  `gh search issues ...` (Fetch Issues)\n\nThis requires the agent to parse intermediate outputs (like the repo list) to construct subsequent commands, leading to multiple tool calls and potential user interruptions.\n\n## proposed_solution\nCreate a unified Python script: `.agent/scripts/check_full_status.py` and refactor repository discovery logic.\n\n### 1. Refactor Common Logic (New Module)\nRefactor the distinct logic from `list_overlay_repos.py` into a reusable library, e.g., `.agent/scripts/lib/workspace.py`.\n-   **Benefit**: Avoids code duplication. Both `list_overlay_repos.py` and the new status script will import this.\n-   **Function**: `get_overlay_repos()` will return the structured list of all workspace repositories.\n\n### 2. Unified Status Script (`check_full_status.py`)\nThis script will:\n1.  **Import Repos**: Use the new `workspace` module to get the target repo list.\n2.  **Local Check**: Execute `status_report.sh` (or implement equivalent logic within the script for tighter integration).\n3.  **Remote Check Strategy**:\n    -   **Constraint**: searching by `user:rolker` is simpler but fetches *all* user activity (including personal/unrelated repos), requiring heavy client-side filtering.\n    -   **Optimization**: We will stick to `repo:owner/name` queries for **server-side filtering**, which is clearer and more efficient (avoids fetching unrelated data).\n    -   **Batching**: If the repository list exceeds command-line limits, the script will automatically batch queries (e.g., 10 repos per call).\n4.  **Reporting**: Output a consolidated Markdown report.\n\n### User Interaction Improvements\n| Metric | Current | Proposed |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **User Approvals** | 3-5 | **1** |\n| **Agent Turns** | ~10 | **2** |\n| **Reliability** | Low (manual pipe) | High (scripted logic) |\n\n## implementation_steps\n1.  **Refactor**: Create `.agent/scripts/lib/__init__.py` and `.agent/scripts/lib/workspace.py` with `get_overlay_repos`.\n2.  **Update**: Modify `.agent/scripts/list_overlay_repos.py` to use the new lib.\n3.  **Create**: Implement `.agent/scripts/check_full_status.py`.\n4.  **Document**: Update `.agent/workflows/ops/check-status.md`.\n\n## decision_needed\nDo you want me to:\n1.  Open an issue to track this enhancement?\n2.  Proceed with implementing the script immediately?","files":null}]}